3. Restrictions

   You may NOT:

   a) Redistribute the software — in source or binary form — as a
      standalone product, as a component marketed or provided to third
      parties within another product, or as a service, whether free or
      paid.

      The following do not constitute redistribution or offering the
      software as a service:

      - Using the software to manage databases for your own products
        or services, whether you or your customers host those databases.

      - Providing setup, configuration, or implementation services that
        enable a licensed user to operate the software for their own
        use.

      However, operating the software on an ongoing basis on behalf of
      third parties — such as providing perpetual database management,
      maintenance, or migration services where SchemaSmith is the
      primary tool — is considered offering the software as a service
      and is not permitted under this license.

   b) Offer the software as a hosted or managed service (SaaS, PaaS,
      or similar) where third parties interact with SchemaSmith
      functionality.

   c) Remove, alter, or obscure any copyright notices, license text,
      or attribution.

   d) Use the SchemaSmith name, logo, or branding to imply endorsement
      of your product or service.

   For clarity: using SchemaSmith to manage databases for your own
   products is always permitted, whether you or your customers host
   those databases. Consultants may help you set up and configure
   SchemaSmith — but ongoing database management using SchemaSmith
   must be performed by your own organization, not outsourced to a
   third party as a perpetual service.

